Two people were killed in a head-on collision on Inanda Road near Hillcrest in Durban on Saturday evening, paramedics said. Paramedics from ER24 arrived on the scene at about 6pm where they found two vehicles had collided head-on, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. Two male occupants were found with fatal injuries in one of the vehicles. Two occupants from the other vehicle sustained moderate injuries. They were treated by another service on [the] scene and later transported to a nearby hospital. The circumstances surrounding the collision were not yet known, he said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter .